The forecast for the Comrades Marathon on Saturday has a chance of rain. Courtesy of #DSTV403 DURBAN - Runners in the Comrade Marathon could be running through the rain on Sunday morning if the weather forecast proves accurate. The marathon spans 89km from Durban to Pietermaritzburg. READ: Mthembu, Steyn bag Two Oceans Marathon title The race is scheduled to begin at 5.30am on Sunday. The Comrades Marathon Association (CMA) has confirmed that nearly R4.3-million for the prize money for the 94th edition of the world’s most gruelling ultramarathon, to be hosted in two weeks’ time.